quran[13]{c,v,t}:
  19,52,And We called him from the right (hand) side of the Mount Toor and drew him nearer for secret talk
  19,53,"And We granted to him from Our mercy, his brother Harun, a prophet"
  19,54,"And mention in the book (about) Ismael, he was truthful in his promise and he was a messenger, a prophet"
  19,55,And he used to enjoin on his people worship (salat) and charity (zakat) and he was one with whom his Fosterer was pleased
  19,56,"And mention in the book (about) Idris, he was a truthful man, a prophet"
  19,57,and We raised him to a high place
  19,58,"Those are the persons on whom Allah bestowed (His) favour, from among the prophets from the descendants of Adam and from among those whom We carried with Nuh (in the ship) and from among the descendants of Ibrahim and Israel and from among those whom We guided and chose, when the communications of the Beneficent (Allah) were read to them they fell down prostrating and weeping"
  19,59,"But the successors who succeeded after them wasted their worship (salat) and followed lusty desires, so they will meet (the punishment for their) error"
  19,60,"except him who repents and believes and does righteous work, so those will enter the garden and they will not be dealt with unjustly in anything"
  19,61,"gardens of everlasting bliss which the Beneficent (Allah) has promised to His servants in the unseen, His promise will certainly come to pass"
  19,62,"Therein they will not hear (any) vain talk but peace, and therein there will be their provision for them morning and evening"
  19,63,That is the garden which We will make (those of) Our servants to inherit who had guarded (against evil)
  19,64,"And we do not come down but by the command of your Fosterer, to Him belongs whatever is before us and whatever is behind us and whatever is between that, and your Fosterer is not forgetful"